text: Champ is an unincorporated community in Audrain County, in the U.S. state of Missouri. ==History== A post office called Champ was established in 1894, and remained in operation until 1901. The community was named after Champ Clark, a state legislator. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Audrain County, Missouri Category:Unincorporated communities in Missouri
title: Champ, Audrain County, Missouri
